        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 4:51PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
northeast of Ashland, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Pittsburg...
Kiowa...                          Alderson...
Blanco...                         Dow...
Bache...                          Ashland...
Savanna...                        Haileyville...
Mcalester...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
